RACE.FOOTNOTES: WINTER'S GHOST raced in the three path around the first turn, tracked the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the far turn, raced in tight quarters approaching the quarter pole, kicked clear and dueled to the wire to hold the win. HEFFNER saved ground around the first turn, led the way on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn, raced in tight quarters and steadied near the quarter pole and weakened further in the final furlong. EXACTING pressed the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn in the two path, was squeezed in tight quarters and stumbled approaching the quarter pole, steadied and faded from there. PIYPA DE LYNDA raced in the two path around the first bend, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path and was empty in the lane.
